\f1\b  The Real Lutheran Church\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \'97-\
The Lutheran Church\'97Missouri Synod (LCMS), by confession, ought to stand under sola scriptura, sola gratia, and sola fide, with the office of the ministry (ministerium verbi) functioning as a servant of the Word\'97not as a prince over the people. But in many corners of the Synod, a subtle inversion has taken place.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf2 \uc0\u9881 \u65039 
\f2  Reframed Observation:\
\
What may feel like \'93clericalistic pastor worship\'94 is, at root, the result of:\
	\'95	Fear of the laity\'92s incompetence (a Gnostic view)\
	\'95	Insecurity in the office, masked by overcompensation\
	\'95	A drift from Word-driven confidence to tradition-driven deference\
	\'95	A misreading of apostolic authority as pastoral sovereignty\
\

\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u57088 
\f2  Cultic Signs:\
	\'95	Unquestionable authority of the pastor over local decisions, even beyond Scripture.\
	\'95	Hostile suspicion of lay initiative, especially in teaching or creative work.\
	\'95	Liturgical formalism elevated as orthodoxy itself, rather than as a form serving the Gospel.\
	\'95	Clergy-only reverence for truth, leaving the laity functionally voiceless.\
\

\f0 \uc0\u9889 
\f2 Counterpoint from Lutheran Orthodoxy:\
	\'95	Walther\'92s \'93Church and Ministry\'94 defends the office but grounds it firmly in the priesthood of all believers.\
	\'95	The Confessions state clearly that the Church exists where the Gospel is preached and the Sacraments are administered\'97not where a particular man stands in robes.\
	\'95	Luther did not suffer fools who replaced one pope with a thousand mini-popes in cassocks.\
\

\f0 \uc0\u10024 
\f2 The Better Way:\
	\'95	Pastors are gifts\'97but not gods.\
	\'95	The strength of the office lies in its weakness: standing only under the Word, not over the congregation.\
	\'95	A true Lutheran pastor lifts up Christ and the Word, not himself.\
\
