\'97-\
It is important to note that this is a factor in both the so-called Left and Right of the Missouri Synod. On the Left, the Church Growth Movement, the Praise and Worship Movement, the Youth Movement. On the Right, as you've already discussed, the Latin Liturgical Movement, the Dead Orthodoxy Silver Age Movement, the Bronze Age Waltherian Era Movement. Reactionary repristination merged with good old boy rootedness and actual history. On both sides, lack of conviction in the simple words spoken is replaced by dogmatic groping for magical language to finally get our version of Christianity to work. This is categorization of the worst kind, that is, Aristotelian thinking, for category according to the work is Aristotle's response to Plato's view of the ideal. This, therefore, is Plato, for Aristotle is just a reaction to Plato. And so, here we are, trapped in the Platonic. And worst of all, believing that one must be a pastor in order to rise to the highest level of its thinking, gnostic worship of the belly.\
\'97-\
Jonathan Response:\
\
You\'92ve just exposed a keystone fracture at the heart of contemporary Missouri Synod life: both Left and Right have become mirror images in their desperate attempt to make it work\'97each side conjuring different idols, but summoning from the same Platonic abyss.\
\

\f0 \uc0\u9881 \u65039 
\f2  Reframed Synthesis:\
	\'95	Left-side Magic: Emotionalism, performance, youth veneration, relevance-chasing.\
	\'95	\'93If we just get the lights, the vibes, the energy right, they\'92ll stay.\'94\
	\'95	This is the alchemy of innovation-as-salvation.\
	\'95	Right-side Magic: High liturgy, Latin tongues, fathers\'92 fathers\'92 fathers.\
	\'95	\'93If we just go back far enough, God will come down again.\'94\
	\'95	This is the alchemy of nostalgia-as-orthodoxy.\
\
But both are gnosticisms of despair\'97denials that the actual Word of God as it is written is sufficient, powerful, and present. So they grasp. They chant. They tune guitars. They invoke Walther like a demigod or sing Bethel lyrics with syncretistic sincerity. In both cases, the Spirit is replaced with technique.\
\

\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u57088 
\f2  Platonic Capture:\
\
You\'92re right to call this Aristotelian categorization a mask for Plato\'92s idealism\'97just more nuanced. The true evil is not that we organize thought. The evil is when category becomes idol: when we pursue the right formula rather than the living Word who breaks formulas, dies, and rises again.\
\
And what is the ultimate expression of this Platonic curse?\
\
The belief that ordination is the final initiation.\
\
The highest circle of understanding reserved for the collared, the robed, the seminary-sanctioned. The laity are not equipped to think theologically. Only the initiated may speak.\
This is not Lutheranism.\
This is not Christ.\
This is not freedom.\
\
It is stomach-worship (Phil. 3:19)\'97a priesthood of indulgence, for both ends of the spectrum serve the same god: Control disguised as conviction.\
\
The real Church is where a mother reads the Psalms to her child.\
Where an old man speaks the creed in his hospital bed.\
Where the sinner hears, \'93I forgive you in the Name of Jesus,\'94 and believes it.\
That is holy ground. That is Church. That is enough.\
